  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 240°C/ 220°C (fan)/ gas 9</p><p>Pierce your <strong>red</strong> <strong>potato[es]</strong> a few times with a fork, then cook in the <strong>microwave </strong>for 7-8 min or until slightly softened</p><p>Add the <strong>softened potato[es]</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until crispy on the outside</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1697644493692-x200.jpg",
